data.description: This is a three unit/three family building with a basement.  There are officially 3 bds in each unit.  The master bedrooms at the front are the largest with EXTRA rooms attached railroad style (like nurseries), but large enough to be additional bdrms on the second and third floors.  The first-floor unit is occupied MTM @ $1600.  The 2nd and 3rd flrs are VACANT!  Both empty floors have recently been remodeled with new sinks, locks, floors, and painting.  This property will bring in income well over the operating expenses.  The bsmnt has a low ceiling and is only for utilities, although there is a new half bath (subway tile photo).  The whole building functions on one furnace and hot water unit.  Irvington code demanded that a room be built around the furnace. The unit provides heat/hot water effectively.  All units have large gas stoves and EIK.  Bathrooms are small.  Second stairwell is on the side of building. The backyard is all concrete and is next to a large lot with grass and trees.
